{"title_page": "More Hearts Than Mine", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = More Hearts Than Mine\n| cover      = IngridAndressMoreHearts.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Ingrid Andress]]\n| album      = [[Lady Like]]\n| released   = July 8, 2019\n| format     = [[Airplay]], [[music download]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Country music|Country]]\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=34}}\n| label      = [[Warner Records|Warner Nashville]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|Ingrid Andress|Sam Ellis|Derrick Southerland}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|Ingrid Andress|Sam Ellis}}\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n}}\n\"'''More Hearts Than Mine'''\" is a song co-written and recorded by American [[country music]] artist [[Ingrid Andress]]. It was released as her debut single in July 2019, following her signing a deal with [[Warner Records|Warner Nashville]] in 2018, and serves as the lead-off single to her debut album ''[[Lady Like]]'', which was released on March 27, 2020.\n\n==Content==\nAndress co-wrote \"More Hearts Than Mine\" with Sam Ellis and Derrick Southerland, which is described as \"a ballad about opening up to heartbreak by inviting a partner to meet your family in your hometown.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theboot.com/ingrid-andress-more-hearts-than-mine-lyrics/|title=Story Behind the Song: Ingrid Andress, 'More Hearts Than Mine'|author=Carena Liptak|date=July 2, 2019|work=|publisher=The Boot|accessdate=November 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n\"More Hearts Than Mine\" debuted at number 59 on the ''Billboard'' [[Country Airplay]] chart dated July 1, 2019.<ref name=\"billboard country update\">{{cite web |url=https://bulletins.billboard.com/country/country_update_0701.pdf |title=Billboard Country Update |work=Billboard |date=July 1, 2019|page=7}}</ref> It debuted at number 88 on the ''Billboard'' [[Hot 100]] chart dated January 11, 2020.<ref>https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100</ref>\n\nThe song was certified Gold by the RIAA on February 27, 2020, for half a million units in sales and streams.{{Certification Cite Ref|region=United States |artist=Ingrid Andress|title=More Hearts Than Mine|type=single}} As of March 2020, the song has sold 105,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web |last=Bjorke |first=Matt |title=Top 30 Digital Country Singles Sales Chart: March 2, 2020|url=http://roughstock.com/news/2020/03/44155-top-30-digital-country-singles-sales-chart-march-2-2020|work=Rough Stock |date=March 4, 2020 |accessdate=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Chart (2019\u20132020)\n! Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|73|artist=Ingrid Andress|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardcanadacountry|4|artist=Ingrid Andress|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardhot100|32|artist=Ingrid Andress|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardcountryairplay|4|artist=Ingrid Andress|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardcountrysongs|8|artist=Ingrid Andress|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US Hot Country Songs (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2019/hot-country-songs|title=Hot Country Songs \u2013 Year-End 2019|work=Billboard|accessdate=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n| 82\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| Various\n| April 5, 2019\n| {{hlist|Digital download}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Warner Records|Warner Nashville]] \n|-\n| July 8, 20